Package org.howard.edu.lsp.assignment4.implementation

Class IntegerSet

java.lang.Object
org.howard.edu.lsp.assignment4.implementation.IntegerSet
public class IntegerSet
extends java.lang.Object
Author:
shaneoliver Class IntegerSet defines a multitude of methods which alter the content of an ArrayList. Each method is described in greater detail below. All ArrayLists declared in the TestFile class are objects of the IntegerSet class.

    • contains

      public boolean contains​(int value)
      Examines set for a specific value. Returns true if value exists in set.
      Parameters:
      value - , the item which this method searches the set for.
      Returns:
      contained, a boolean set to true by default. Maintained as true if value is found in set, else changed to false.

    • largest

      public int largest() throws IntegerSetException
      If set has no length, throws a custom IntegerSetException error.
      Returns:

      Throws:
      IntegerSetException - custom exception class for empty sets.

      IntegerSetException - custom exception class for empty sets.
